    <text id="A8050T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>H. M. Bell informs John McCue that he is now one of McCue's creditors.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1860-01-11">Jany 11<hi rend="underline">th</hi> 1860</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>John H. McCue <abbr expan="Esquire">Esq</abbr></salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your note to Kayser Stribling &amp; <abbr expan="Company">Co</abbr> for
                    $211.86 dated <abbr expan="November">Nov.</abbr> 1/57 has fallen into my hands
                    as Trustee by the assignment of John W. Stribling. I of course do not wish
                    &amp; will not do anything to annoy you in reference to this note, but will
                    hold it very much to suit your convenience, and hope you will be able to relieve
                    me by from time to time paying in such amounts as you can conveniently do. I am
                    one of the sufferers myself by Striblings failure &amp; wish to realize as
                    much as possible out of the assets, and know that you will do all you can in the
                        <unclear>premises</unclear>. Please advise.</p>
                <p>Remember me to Cousin Liz:</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>In haste<lb/>Very Truly Your friend</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">H. M. Bell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
